<TITLE> Bangladesh denies Indian charges of delaying Dhaka-Kolkata trains </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 24 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Wednesday trashed Indian allegation of dragging its heels on introduction of direct passenger trains between Dhaka and Kolkata. Indian high commissioner Pinak Ranjan Chakravarty at a business dialogue in city Sunday alleged that Bangladesh was showing 'reluctance' to introduce Dhaka-Kolkata train service. "Discussions are ongoing and a draft of the agreement on the passenger train service has been sent to the Indian authorities from the Bangladesh side," said a foreign ministry press statement signed by senior assistant secretary Maushumi Rahman. "A response is awaited from the Indian side," it said. "It must be understood that on this or any other negotiations with a particular country, Bangladesh will always seek to protect her perceived national interest," the statement said. bd
